- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on the impact of social bots on online communication during a protest movement on Twitter. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is also likely as the paper discusses the societal implications of social bots on online communication. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is a possible category as the paper touches on the use of bot detection tools to classify accounts using the protest hashtag. 
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is a possible category as the paper may discuss the development and implementation of the BotOrNot bot detection tool. 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper may discuss the computational methods used to analyze the data on the protest hashtag and social bots.
